parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire belt separation can cause the tire to fail, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
Tire sidewall cracking can lead to tire failure, loss of vehicle control, and potential accidents.
symptoms: Visible cracks on the tire sidewall

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation can cause the tire to fail, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or crash, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The transmission jumps out of gear
or hesitates to shift; the vehicle stalls or loses power; unusual noises or vibrations occur while shifting; the transmission fluid leaks or is contaminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Drive shaft failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or crash, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: especially during acceleration; the drive shaft makes unusual noises or feels loose; the vehicle pulls to one side or loses power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Clutch failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or crash, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy; the clutch pedal sticks to the floor; the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position; the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Gear shift indicator failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or crash, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The gear shift indicator does not function properly; the vehicle shifts into the wrong gear; the vehicle crashes or loses power.

and temperature gauges drop to zero or get stuck
the digital mileage disappears or skews.
